    <content_encoded><![CDATA[<p>We will be tabling at this yearâ€™s <a href="http://bayareaanarchistbookfair.wordpress.com">Bay Area Book Fair</a> on March 22, as we have for over a decade. We will bring the <a href="http://www.crimethinc.com/blog/2014/03/03/rolling-thunder-11-shipping-soon/">brand new issue of Rolling Thunder</a> and a great deal of other exciting material. One of the authors of our zine <a href="http://www.crimethinc.com/blog/2013/09/06/new-zine-about-self-care-self-as-other/"><em>Self as Other</em></a> will be presenting the workshop <a href="http://bayareaanarchistbookfair.wordpress.com/2014-session-descriptions/">"Beyond Self-Care: The Subversive Potential of Care"</a>. That evening, <a href="http://www.crimethinc.com/blog/2013/06/29/catharsis-discography-repress-and-tour/">Catharsis</a> will be playing <a href="http://www.oaklandmetro.org/event/164767">a single West Coast reunion show</a>. If you live in the area, we hope to see you at one of these events! Stay tuned for Crimethinc. activities on at least three continents in April.</p>

